cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.LG. 

The paper focuses on recognizing and analyzing the layout, detecting and recognizing textlines and characters of large historical document collections. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for layout analysis and character recognition, information retrieval (cs.IR) for analyzing the content of the documents, natural language processing (cs.CL) for text recognition, deep learning (cs.DL) for training models, and machine learning (cs.LG) for developing algorithms.
